   significantly to N addition. The common hypothesis that tropical forests
   do not respond to N because they are phosphorus-limited could not be
   confirmed, as we found no significant response to phosphorus addition in
   tropical forests. Across climate zones, we found that young forests
   responded more strongly to N addition, which is important as many
